        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-blue-gray-900 mt-10 mb-4">Fellowship Benefits</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
            Each fellowship includes:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 mb-6">
            <li>
                <strong>Complimentary Forum registration</strong> (valued at $800)</li>
            <li>
                <strong>Three nights' accommodation</strong> at the conference hotel (Nov. 16–19; valued at $850)</li>
            <li>
                <strong>$650 travel and incidentals stipend</strong>
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Invitations to exclusive networking opportunities</strong>
            </li>
        </ul>

        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">Fellows will be asked to contribute a brief (up to 1,000 words) reflection on their experience for publication on the DLF blog.</p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-blue-gray-900 mt-10 mb-4">Who Should Apply?</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
            Fellowships are open to applicants from across the library, archives, museum, cultural heritage, and digital humanities fields. You may apply for an award in multiple categories but can only be selected for one. Former DLF Forum fellows are not eligible.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-blue-gray-900 mt-10 mb-4">Fellowship Categories</h2>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-blue-gray-900 mt-10 mb-4">Students and New Professionals</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
            For current students pursuing degrees in, or exploring careers related to, libraries, archives, museums, cultural heritage, or digital humanities.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-blue-gray-900 mt-10 mb-4">Emerging Professionals</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
            For individuals who graduated in May 2023 or later and are pursuing careers in libraries, archives, cultural heritage, or digital humanities.
        </p>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-blue-gray-900 mt-10 mb-4">HBCU Students and Workers</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
            For librarians, faculty, and other employees affiliated with a White House designated Historically Black College of University (HBCU), as well as current HBCU students interested in library and information careers.
        </p>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-blue-gray-900 mt-10 mb-4">Public Library Workers</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
            For librarians and paraprofessional staff currently employed at public libraries who work with digital services and collections or scholarly communications.
        </p>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-blue-gray-900 mt-10 mb-4">Grassroots Archives and Cultural Heritage Workers</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
            For individuals who work or volunteer in community, grassroots, or participatory archives, or organizations focused on community-centric history, heritage, and memory projects.
        </p>

